{ This is the best placement for the knight. On f3 it protects e5 and is well centralized. }
16... Rfe8 17. Bf4
{ Next, White is going to place the rooks on c1 and d1 with pressure on the hanging pawns. }
17... f6 { This move is always dangerous, but it doesn't work here. } 18. Qd3
{ Simple and effective. White's pawn is still protected and Black has merely weakened their kingside. }
