{ We come to the end of a long line, which however has been very interesting to study. White should have the upper hand here, as our piece activity is greater. I understand that it's not easy to win from this position, but thats just the way things are when two players know their theory and play correctly.   A@@EndBracket@@  22...Rf3+?  Going for the g3-pawn is very problematic for Black.  23.Bd3  Rxg3  24.Re5!  ↑  White threatens to take on a5 and also Rg5+!, which is a big problem for Black. After 22.Kc3 the position was close to equal, and just a few inaccurate moves later White is already clearly better.   B@@EndBracket@@  22...Rxa2  23.Bd3→  Creating many targets for White. Our compensation is visible.   C@@EndBracket@@  22...d5!  is the best move. The endgame is very complicated after  23.Re7!  ↑ }
