{ The only reason I am including this position is because it was played in a game between two GMs: 1-0 @@StartBracket@@34@@EndBracket@@ Brodsky,D @@StartBracket@@2455@@EndBracket@@-Hong,A @@StartBracket@@2474@@EndBracket@@ Saint Louis USA 2021. }
12. Qc2 { Forcing the knight to immediately move again. } 12... Nb6 13. Nd2
{ Always a flexible move! White keeps giving up pawns, but Black cannot really take them. }
13... fxe5
{ 13...O-O-O  14.Re3  Using the rook, this move is important because it forces Black to keep the e-file closed. Keeping the center files closed is huge for White, because our initiative is mainly on the queenside. By closing the center we limit Black's counterplay there.  14...fxe5  15.Nf3± }
14. Ne4
{ Once again, we give up a pawn for the initiative. In this line we are two tempi ahead of a typical line because of Black's ...Nd5-b4-d5 waste of time. }
