1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. e5 Qe7 7. Qe2 Nd5 8.
h4 f6
{ This is the most complicated line against 8.h4! Against this move we will use the famous Rh3 idea! What makes this position so complex is that White will sacrifice a pawn for the initiative. For humans this is always difficult to understand, so if you practice the lines in this chapter and truly understand the arising positions, your opponents will have a really tough time. }
9. c4 Ba6 { By far the best move, and the only one played by top players. } 10.
Rh3 Nb6
{ The reason I don't like this move is because Black doesn't need to move the knight yet, so why waste an important tempo in the opening? Well, Black removes the knight from the c4 attack and is now ready to take the pawn on e5 or even play ...d5. The knight on b6 also puts pressure on the c4-pawn. So it's not illogical at all - in fact, this move has been played by many GMs. }
11. exf6
{ This is the simplest reply! You can opt for a more agressive pawn sac with  11.Nd2  , but if you like endgames  11.exf6  could be your move. }
11... Qxe2+ 12. Bxe2 Bxc4
{ The only way. Back needs to take on c4, otherwise it gets bad for them really fast. }
13. Re3+
{ A tricky move! Black has to define the king, and there is only one way to go. }
13... Kf7
{ This brings the king into an attack from White's pieces, and it makes no sense. }
14. fxg7 Bxg7 15. Bh5+
{ Forcing Black to move the king back and disconnecting their rooks. This will give White more time to fully develop and take advantage of the initiative. }
15... Kf8
{ This was played between Ivan Cheparinov and Gawain Jones in Hengshui 2019. This is a worse version of  15...Kg8  because Black doesn't have any useful moves like Bf7 which they do with the King on g8. }
16. Nc3
{ Always go back to the basics when possible. If things are calm, let's not forget to finish our development and castle. }
16... Kg8
{ One of the things White needs to avoid is to make too many trades, especially of those pieces that are active like the bishops and the rook on the 3rd rank. }
17. Rg3
{ Now if  17...Bf7  18.Bh6!  is similar to the main line with 15...Kg8. } *

