12... O-O-O 13. Ra3
{ It's now time to bring the rook to the a-file. With the black King on the queenside, this rook is defintely on the right square. we also attack a6 and a7, already creating visible issues in Black's position.   13.Rb3!?  is also very good as it stops Black's king from going to b8 or their queen from going to b4. Moreover, we are now ready to continue developing with Nc3 and O-O-O. A more aggressive idea is to play Qd2-Qa5.  13...d5  14.Nd2  Protecting c4 and trying to castle long.  14...dxc4  15.g3!  ↑  A beautiful move, targeting the h3-c8 diagonal and using the power of the pin on the f1-a6 diagonal. The position is complicated, but White has the initiative for sure. }
