11... d5 12. Nd2 dxc4 13. g3
{ There is no rush with regaining the pawn, as Black's doubled isolated pawns won't run away. Now, castling short seems the best way to coordinate White's pieces. }
13... Be6 14. Bg2 Qc7
{ Black needs to castle short, as going long looks very risky. } 15. O-O
{ From this position there have been 2 games played at the 2600 level and they were both draws, but I believe White can do better. A plan like Nf3-g5-d4 or Rac1 followed by b3 to target c6 are both possible. White can also simply take on b6 and recover the c4-pawn. -   15.h5!?  was played recently, and is a new idea that could be quite exciting. White threatens h6 and a possible Rh4 lift. ½-½ @@StartBracket@@23@@EndBracket@@ Esipenko,A @@StartBracket@@2683@@EndBracket@@-Artemiev,V @@StartBracket@@2697@@EndBracket@@ St Petersburg RUS 2023  15...h6  16.Bh3↑  Exchanging the bishop on e6 which is acting as the defender of the c4-pawn. White has some initiative! }
15... Bb4 16. b3 cxb3 17. Nxb3
{ With intense pressure on the c6-pawn. White's pieces are simply better placed. }
