1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. e5 Nd5
{ A bit of a surprise move! Plenty of times this comes as a premove on online chess or simply Black got the order wrong, but luckily for them, it's an acceptable move. There was no point for White to play Qe2 because Black didn't force us to protect e5 so we took advantage of it and quickly kicked the knight. }
7. c4
{ We obviously don't like the knight on d5, and we want to define it as soon as possible. This allows us to move quickly into developing and with more control of the space. }
7... Nb6 8. Bd3
{ I like the simplicity of this move, we just want to short castle and play with the pawn structure advantage. Coordinating is still our top priority.   8.Be3!?  ⩲ A more complex development is also great for White!  8...Bb4+  9.Nd2!  ⩲  This looks as good as the main line! White will follow with Bd3 or Qc2 or both, then castle O-O or O-O-O. The Black bishop on b4 at that time will be useless.  9...O-O  10.Bd3!  Re8  Here we don't have time to castle long, but that's ok!  11.O-O !  ±  Rxe5  12.Nf3↑ }
8... g6
{ A good way to develop so that White's attack on the kingside is blocked by the g6-pawn.   8...Bc5?!  doesn't help Black in any way.  9.O-O  O-O  10.Nd2!  ± }
9. h4
{ In this course, we are all about h4! Threatening the usual stuff! 10. h5 or maybe 10. Bg5. I wouldn't disregard a Rh3! }
9... d5
{ Black responds as usual! When things get difficult, let's break the center!   9...Be7?  Too slow!  10.h5+-   9...Bg7?  Now this move is not possible!  10.Bg5!!  f6  Forced!  11.exf6  Bxf6  12.Qe2+!  Kf7   12...Qe7??  13.Bxf6+-  13.Nc3!  White is now back to castling long since we have a powerful attack on the kingside, and we are fully coordinated to do so.  13...Re8  A move to worry about, but it doesn't help Black's case.  14.Ne4!  d5  15.Bxf6+- }
10. cxd5
{ It seems like in this line it's more precise to keep taking the d-pawn with the c-pawn.   10.exd6!?  is again good!  10...Qxd6  11.O-O  ⩲ }
10... cxd5
{ The most logical move!  10...Bg7  is the best move for Black but very unclear why? We can just continue taking pawns.  11.dxc6⩲   10...Nxd5?  It makes things worse for Black. }
11. Bg5
{ A remarkable move to force the bishop to go to e7. Moving the queen will make things worst for Black.   11.h5!?  Almost any move here is good for White. }
11... Be7 12. Bh6
{ We now stop the Black king from castling, and that bishop is simply frustrating on h6! The big trick here is that you cannot take on h4!  12...Bxh4??  13.Bb5++- }
