12... Bg4
{ This is Black's most played move in this position, but it's not a dangerous one. Black is lacking space and piece mobility, so it makes sense for them to try to trade off some minor pieces. }
13. Be2
{ This move is very natural because it develops and defends at the same time. }
13... Nf5
{ A nice tactical way to improve piece activity, giving Black some chances. }
14. Qxe4 { It's time to get our pawn back! } 14... Bxe2 15. Qxe2
