9. Qd2
{ The most natural move. Another good thing about Qd2 is that it doesn't allow Black to play ...Nd4. }
9... Be6
{ A natural approach, speeding up development to finally castle queenside. }
10. O-O-O Qd7 11. Bb5
{ An important move to create pressure and stop Black from castling, since  11...O-O-O?!  is answered by  12.Nd5!  and Black is in trouble, for example  12...f6?  13.Bxf6!  . The bishops are now attacking both of Black's knights and White is fully developed. }
