{ Immediately questioning the g5-bishop and intending to follow up with ...g5 after Bh4. }
8. Bh4 d6
{ This is a very interesting move order because Black wants to keep their options open when it comes to castling. The only downside of this move is that now playing for a quick ...d5 is out of the question. At the same time, White has many ways of playing that are good, so it's hard for Black to get a good position against all of White's options. }
9. Bb5
{ This is very similar to my main recommendation  9.Bd3  . White tries to play Qe2 then castle either way with an easy and straightforward game. }
9... O-O 10. f3
{ Another useful waiting move. We need to protect the e4-pawn sooner or later, so we might as well play this move now. We don't play  10.Qe2  because of the strong reply  10...Nd4  , which would render our previous move Bb5 useless. }
10... a6 11. Bxc6
{ After Black recaptures we can continue with Qe2 and castle on either side. Na4xb6 is always an idea too. }
