1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Bb4+ 5. c3
{ Black's idea is to lure our pawn to c3 so that we can't directly put a knight on c3 anymore. Now, if White wishes to play Nc3, we need to play c4 first. }
5... Bc5 6. Be3 Bb6 7. Nf5
{ The easiest way to play!  7.Qg4  was played by Kasparov and is also interesting, but I like  7.Nf5  better. }
7... Bxe3
{ This is a better version for White than we'll see after  7...g6  . In this case Black doesn't get a half-open a-file. }
8. Nxe3 Nf6 9. f3
{ Followed by  9...--  10.c4  and then Nc3. We'll see the same ideas after 7...g6, except here Black has no half-open a-file. }
