7... d5
{ An aggressive approach to fight for the initiative, but it's not enough. } 8.
exd5 Nb4
{ A double attack targeting c2 and d5. It suddenly looks like Black has huge pressure, but White has a way to escape from all dangers. }
9. Bb5+
{ A forcing move that develops and counters right away. This gives White the option of castling, which then avoids the ...Nxc2+ threat. }
9... c6 10. Qe2+
{ An important in-between move to make Black's position uncomfortable. } 10...
Be7 { The only move! Any other option is really bad for Black. } 11. d6
{ And White has a clear initiative and the better coordination. } *

