7. Bf4
{ A very flexible move! White is waiting for the f8-bishop to move and we get rid of the possibility of ...Bd6. Now Black will need to develop with ...Be7.  7.Bf4  also develops our bishop and keeps everything together. It's the perfect move!   7.Nc3?!  was played by Cheparinov, but I don't see why you would allow Black to play  7...Bb4!  ∞  , so I don't like this approach. 1-0 @@StartBracket@@29@@EndBracket@@ Cheparinov,I @@StartBracket@@2686@@EndBracket@@-Marholev,D @@StartBracket@@2348@@EndBracket@@ Kozloduy 2014 }
