1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nxd4
{ This move is very popular online, but unheard of in top player's games. Black helps White to quickly centralize White's queen, which immediately leads to a very good position for White. }
5. Qxd4 c5
{ Many of my students encounter this move. There is something about attacking a queen with a tempo that makes this move tempting for a lot of black players. This, of course, is really bad strategically because of the weaknesses it creates on the d-file. }
6. Qe3
{ The best square for the queen! We don't want to block the bishop on f1 and we don't to give Black any more tempi. Also, the final placement of the queen will be the active square g3. }
6... d6 7. Nc3 Nf6 8. Qg3
{ Black has problems developing, while we will continue with Bd2 or Bg5 followed by castling long. }
